headline: Cisco Stock Drops After Earnings
summary: Cisco Systems  stock was down after the networking company reported fiscal-fourth quarter financials Wednesday night.  Cisco reported fiscal fourth-quarter adjusted earnings of 99 cents a share on revenue of $14.7 billion.  Revenue for Cisco’s networking segment, which brings in the most revenue for the company and includes gear used in AI data centers, was $7.63 billion, a 12% increase from the prior year.
